// LLVM ANNOTATIONS PASS
// Andy Luong
// Tim Malone

/**********************
// AnnotationPass
**********************/
Currently the pass requires one argument passed to the "-pal" flag indicating where the annotation file will be. It will then print out the annotations.

/**********************
// MAKEFILE
**********************/
The Makefile is very simple. Currently it load the broadway and and c-breeze libraries and links them with the AnnotationPass.
You will need to modify the location of these libraries in order to point to your local builds.

/**********************
// RUN:
**********************/
The follower command will run the AnnotationPass with an annotation file (foo.pal) and a dummy IR file (test.ll).
  opt -load ../../../Debug/lib/AnnotationPass.so -annotation -pal test/foo.pal < ./test/test.ll
